      <akn:section eId="sec_32_1331_09">
        <akn:num>32-1331.09</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Private right of action.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1331_09_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A person aggrieved by a violation of this subchapter, or any rule issued pursuant to this subchapter, by an employer or entity may bring a civil action in any court of competent jurisdiction within 3 years after the occurrence of the alleged violation of [this] subchapter. A person whose rights have been violated under this subchapter by an employer or entity is entitled to collect:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1331_09_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A court may order the following:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1331_09_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The court shall allow for reasonable attorneys fees and costs of the action to be paid by the defendant.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
